crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a cross-platform information stealer written in C++ using the Qt framework. The malware targets sensitive data from Chrome, Brave, and Opera browsers, including the macOS Keychain (`login.keychain-db`), browser `Login Data` files (passwords), and files associated with numerous cryptocurrency wallet extensions (e.g., MetaMask, Binance Wallet, Ronin Wallet). It exfiltrates the stolen data via an HTTP POST request to a hardcoded C2 server at `http://95[.]164[.]17[.]24:1224/uploads`. After exfiltration, it downloads, unpacks (`tar -xf`), and executes a second-stage payload.
